url":"https://api.github.com/users/spettroscopio/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/spettroscopio/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/spettroscopio/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/spettroscopio/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/spettroscopio/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2016-06-20T14:03:24Z","updated_at":"2016-06-20T14:48:58Z","body":"@elmindreda \n\nI would like to add a suggestion.\n\nIf I understood correctly looking at the source glfwGetMonitors() returns the cached configuration retrieved at the initialization of the library or updated when a change monitor event is fired.\n\nWould be possible to add a flag to glfwGetMonitors() (or to add a new separated function if you prefer it) to ask for an update of the current configuration ? In short, to call _glfwPlatformGetMonitors() again.\n\nThis way, since this \"change\" event looks tricky, we would have at least a backup to manually update the configuration when required, for example just before entering a configuration page in our program or similar \"hot\" spots. \n\nI believe it would be a useful fallback to have.\n\nWhat do you think ? Maybe could be a good approach for other cases too (Joysticks ? But I admit I didn't look at that code so maybe it's nor )required) \n\nbtw: thank you to everyone working on this library, it's nice, small, simple to use and looks well written too :-)\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments/227151076/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"spettroscopio","id":19908595,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE5OTA4NTk1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/19908595?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/spettro